  "genie_instructions": "ALWAYS prefer metric views with MEASURE() syntax for aggregation questions. The freight_kpi_monthly view (source: shipping_lanes) has dimensions: shipment_date, commodity, origin_region, shipment_status. Measures: total_carloads, total_revenue, avg_transit_days, shipment_count, delayed_count. The forecast_kpi_monthly view (source: demand_forecasts) has dimensions: forecast_month, commodity, origin_region, model_version. Measures: total_forecasted_carloads, total_actual_carloads, avg_forecast_error, total_forecasted_revenue, forecast_count. Use GROUP BY ALL with MEASURE() queries. Only query base tables directly when the question requires columns not available as metric view dimensions (e.g. lane_id, lane_name).",
  "sample_questions": [
